  "notes": "All 72 group-stage matches (12 groups A-L, 6 matches each) are included. Group/team/score/venue data is sourced primarily from the per-group Wikipedia articles (2026 FIFA World Cup Group A through Group L), which carry per-match scores, kickoff times with local UTC offsets, and venues. FIFA 3-letter codes confirmed via Soccerphile's official FIFA country-code list.\n\nKICKOFF UTC CONVERSION: Source times were given in local stadium time with explicit UTC offsets (EDT=UTC-4, CDT=UTC-5, central Mexico=UTC-6 (no DST), MDT=UTC-6 not used here, PDT=UTC-7). I converted each to UTC ISO 8601. Note that matches in Mexico (Estadio Azteca/Akron/BBVA) use UTC-6 year-round, and US East-coast venues use UTC-4 (EDT). A handful of late-night kickoffs roll over to the next calendar day in UTC (e.g., Group A KOR-CZE local 11 Jun 20:00 CST = 12 Jun 02:00Z).\n\nSTATUS / SCORES HONESTY: Today is the snapshot date 2026-06-25. Matches confirmed FINISHED with scores (48 matches): all of Groups A, B, C; matchdays 1-2 of Groups D, E, F, G, H, I, J, K, L. Group A/B/C final-round results (24 Jun local) were independently cross-confirmed by SBS News' June-25 results page (Mexico 3-0 Czechia, South Africa 1-0 South Korea, Morocco 4-2 Haiti, Brazil 3-0 Scotland, Switzerland 2-1 Canada, Bosnia 3-1 Qatar) matching Wikipedia.\n\nThe 24 matches marked \"scheduled\" with null scores are all matchday-3 fixtures kicking off on/after 25 Jun local time. The Group D, E, F matches on 25 Jun were NOT confirmed finished by any clean authoritative source at snapshot time (some search snippets offered scores for these but were internally inconsistent/garbled, conflating matchday-1 recaps with matchday-3, so per the no-guessing rule I left them null/scheduled). Groups G/H matchday 3 fall on 26 Jun; Groups I matchday 3 on 26 Jun; Groups J/K/L matchday 3 on 27 Jun; Group J on 27 Jun local rolls to 28 Jun UTC. Note Wikipedia listed Group J matchday-3 as 27 Jun 9:00 p.m. UTC-5 = 28 Jun 02:00Z.\n\nCAVEATS: (1) \"Turkey\" is rendered TUR; FIFA/Wikipedia may style it \"Türkiye\". (2) \"Czech Republic\" is styled \"Czechia\" by some sources; code CZE either way. (3) Curaçao code is CUW (not CUR). DR Congo is COD. (4) Some matchday-3 kickoff times may be subject to minor FIFA scheduling adjustments. If live confirmation of the 25-27 Jun results is required, re-check FIFA.com or ESPN closer to those dates."
